{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gv4YZ2WZwFyuKeec72pXfa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Self-Evolution System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Cloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n     6→automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n     7→time. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n     8→completion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n     9→audit trail.\n    10→\n    11→The system draws on the ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) framework for prompt\n    12→evolution — treating prompts as structured, itemized playbooks that accumulate\n    13→lessons rather than monolithic documents that get rewritten.\n    14→\n    15→**Scope (this version):** Additive changes only. Prompt updates, new script\n    16→steps, new agent steps, new wiring. No step removal or mutation of existing step\n    17→definitions.\n    18→\n    19→## Architecture\n    20→\n    21→The evolution system is a multi-stage pipeline with three specialized output\n    22→branches. The LLM handles classification, reflection, and content generation.\n    23→Deterministic Go code handles structural manipulation (DSL editing, file I/O,\n    24→audit logging).\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n    28→                    │         Workflow Run Completes       │\n    29→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    30→                                   │\n    31→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    32→                    │           Collector                  │\n    33→                    │  Gathers: run results, history.log,  │\n    34→                    │  step outputs, knowledge base,       │\n    35→                    │  current prompts + workflow          │\n    36→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    37→                                   │\n    38→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    39→                    │         Classifier (LLM)            │\n    40→                    │  Categorizes run prompt:             │\n    41→                    │  bug | feedback | feature |          │\n    42→                    │  enhancement | chore                 │\n    43→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    44→                                   │\n    45→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    46→                    │         Reflector (LLM)              │\n    47→                    │  ACE-style: examines traces,         │\n    48→                    │  extracts structured lessons          │\n    49→                    │  (bullets with metadata)              │\n    50→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    51→                                   │\n    52→              ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n    53→              │                    │                     │\n    54→   ┌──────────▼────────┐ ┌────────▼──────────┐ ┌───────▼──────────┐\n    55→   │  Prompt Curator    │ │  Script Generator │ │  DSL Mutator     │\n    56→   │  (LLM + dedup)     │ │  (LLM)            │ │  (Go code)       │\n    57→   │                    │ │                    │ │                   │\n    58→   │  Merges lessons    │ │  Writes new        │ │  Adds steps,     │\n    59→   │  into prompt files │ │  checker/linter    │ │  wiring, collects │\n    60→   │  as structured     │ │  scripts           │ │  to .cloche file  │\n    61→   │  bullets           │ │                    │ │                   │\n    62→   └────────┬───────────┘ └────────┬───────────┘ └───────┬──────────┘\n    63→            │                      │                      │\n    64→            └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n    65→                                   │\n    66→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    67→                    │         Audit Logger                 │\n    68→                    │  Records all changes + reasons        │\n    69→                    │  Updates knowledge base summary       │\n    70→                    │  Snapshots pre-change state           │\n    71→                    └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→The three branches fire independently based on lesson category. A single\n    75→evolution pass may produce changes across multiple branches, or none at all.\n    76→\n    77→## Multi-Project Scoping\n    78→\n    79→The daemon supports multiple concurrent cloche instances across different\n    80→projects (and multiple runs within the same project). Every run record includes\n    81→`project_dir` — the absolute path to the project directory where `cloche run`\n    82→was invoked.\n    83→\n    84→All evolution state is scoped by project_dir + workflow_name:\n    85→- SQLite queries filter by project_dir\n    86→- Knowledge bases live at `<project_dir>/.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n    87→- Evolution passes for different projects/workflows run independently\n    88→- One evolution pass at a time per project+workflow (mutex)\n    89→\n    90→## Data Collection\n    91→\n    92→### New Signals Captured Per Run\n    93→\n    94→| Signal               | Where captured                        | Notes                          |\n    95→|----------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n    96→| Assembled prompt     | Prompt adapter, before LLM invocation | Full text sent to the agent    |\n    97→| Agent stdout         | Prompt adapter, after agent returns   | Full LLM response              |\n    98→| Run prompt class     | Classifier LLM, post-run             | bug/feedback/feature/etc.      |\n    99→| Retry count per step | Prompt adapter attempt tracking       | Already in filesystem, add to SQLite |\n   100→| Project directory    | CLI sends to daemon via gRPC          | Currently implicit             |\n   101→\n   102→### Run Prompt Classification\n   103→\n   104→The Classifier examines each run's `--prompt` text and categorizes it:\n   105→\n   106→- **bug** — fixing something broken; indicates a gap the system should reflect on\n   107→  for patterns in its approach to software development\n   108→- **feedback** — code review style issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture); things\n   109→  caught in a typical review cycle that the system should watch its output for\n   110→- **feature** — new functionality; normal work\n   111→- **enhancement** — improving existing functionality\n   112→- **chore** — maintenance; no evolution signal\n   113→\n   114→Bug and feedback runs are the primary evolution drivers. Features and\n   115→enhancements provide background context but don't typically trigger changes.\n   116→Classification happens via LLM inference on the prompt text — no explicit\n   117→`--type` flag needed from the user.\n   118→\n   119→### SQLite Schema Additions\n   120→\n   121→```sql\n   122→-- Add project scoping to runs\n   123→ALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '';\n   124→\n   125→-- Extend step_executions with captured data\n   126→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN prompt_text TEXT;\n   127→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN agent_output TEXT;\n   128→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN attempt_number INTEGER DEFAULT 1;\n   129→\n   130→-- Track evolution passes\n   131→CREATE TABLE evolution_log (\n   132→    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   133→    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL,\n   134→    workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   135→    trigger_run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n   136→    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL,\n   137→    classification TEXT,\n   138→    changes_json TEXT NOT NULL,\n   139→    knowledge_delta TEXT\n   140→);\n   141→```\n   142→\n   143→### On-Disk Evolution State\n   144→\n   145→```\n   146→.cloche/\n   147→  evolution/\n   148→    log.jsonl                   # append-only audit trail (one JSON object per line)\n   149→    knowledge/\n   150→      develop.md                # ACE-style knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n   151→    snapshots/\n   152→      <timestamp>-<filename>    # pre-change backups for revert\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→## Pipeline Stages\n   156→\n   157→### Stage 1: Collector\n   158→\n   159→Triggers after every run completion. Gathers:\n   160→\n   161→1. All runs for this project+workflow since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   162→   `evolution_log.trigger_run_id`)\n   163→2. The accumulated knowledge base (`knowledge/<workflow>.md`)\n   164→3. Current prompt files referenced by the workflow\n   165→4. The current `.cloche` workflow DSL file\n   166→5. Runs classified as \"bug\" or \"feedback\" carry more weight in analysis\n   167→\n   168→If there are no new runs since the last evolution, the pipeline short-circuits.\n   169→\n   170→### Stage 2: Classifier (LLM)\n   171→\n   172→For each unclassified run, the Classifier examines the run prompt and assigns a\n   173→category. The classification is stored in the run record (SQLite) for use by the\n   174→Reflector and for future queries.\n   175→\n   176→### Stage 3: Reflector (LLM)\n   177→\n   178→The Reflector examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons. It\n   179→receives the collected run data (step results, failure logs, retry counts), the\n   180→current knowledge base, and the current prompts and workflow.\n   181→\n   182→It produces delta entries — structured lessons:\n   183→\n   184→```json\n   185→{\n   186→  \"lessons\": [\n   187→    {\n   188→      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-001\",\n   189→      \"category\": \"prompt_improvement\",\n   190→      \"target\": \"prompts/implement.md\",\n   191→      \"insight\": \"Agent consistently produces unsanitized HTML output in form handlers. 4 of last 6 bug-type runs involved XSS.\",\n   192→      \"suggested_action\": \"Add explicit rule: always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\n   193→      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\", \"run-ghi\", \"run-jkl\"],\n   194→      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n   195→    },\n   196→    {\n   197→      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-002\",\n   198→      \"category\": \"new_step\",\n   199→      \"step_type\": \"script\",\n   200→      \"insight\": \"No static security analysis in workflow. Security bugs only caught by user reports post-deployment.\",\n   201→      \"suggested_action\": \"Add gosec script step after test, wire failures to fix\",\n   202→      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\"],\n   203→      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n   204→    }\n   205→  ]\n   206→}\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→Confidence levels (high/medium/low) are based on evidence count and pattern\n   210→consistency. Only lessons meeting the configured minimum confidence proceed to\n   211→the executor branches.\n   212→\n   213→**Knowledge base deduplication:** After confidence filtering, the Reflector\n   214→cross-references generated lesson IDs against the current knowledge base text.\n   215→Lessons whose ID already appears in the knowledge base are dropped, preventing\n   216→the same lessons from being re-surfaced across evolution cycles. The\n   217→Orchestrator applies a second-layer ID filter as a guard, ensuring that even if\n   218→the Reflector misses a duplicate, previously applied lessons are not\n   219→re-processed.\n   220→\n   221→### Stage 4: Executor Branches\n   222→\n   223→Based on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n   224→\n   225→#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n   226→\n   227→Handles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n   228→\n   229→- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n   230→- **Content-change guard:** Before calling the LLM, the curator checks whether\n   231→  the lesson's key insight or suggested action is already present in the current\n   232→  prompt text (case-insensitive substring match). If the lesson is already\n   233→  incorporated, the curator returns immediately without calling the LLM and\n   234→  without rewriting the file. This prevents churn, snapshot bloat, and\n   235→  regression risk from unnecessary rewrites.\n   236→- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n   237→  bullet/rule\n   238→- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n   239→  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n   240→- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n   241→  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n   242→  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n   243→- Conversational response validation: after stripping code fences, the output is\n   244→  checked for conversational markers (e.g. \"I need write permission\", \"Here is\n   245→  the updated prompt:\", \"Could you grant access\"). If the LLM returned\n   246→  meta-conversation text instead of prompt content, the curator falls back to\n   247→  appending the lesson directly as a structured bullet rather than trusting the\n   248→  LLM output. This prevents prompt file corruption when the LLM produces\n   249→  interactive-style responses.\n   250→- **Post-write sanity check:** After writing the updated prompt to disk, the\n   251→  curator re-reads the file and validates it: the content must be non-empty,\n   252→  must not start with conversational phrases, and must contain at least one\n   253→  markdown heading (`#`). If the sanity check fails, the curator restores the\n   254→  file from the pre-change snapshot and returns a `prompt_update_rollback`\n   255→  change entry instead of `prompt_update`. The snapshot is preserved as\n   256→  evidence.\n   257→- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n   258→\n   259→#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n   260→\n   261→Handles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n   262→\n   263→- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n   264→- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n   265→  prompt file for agent steps\n   266→- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n   267→  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n   268→- Output: the file path and content\n   269→\n   270→#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n   271→\n   272→Handles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\n   273→them to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n   274→\n   275→**Add Step Definition:**\n   276→```json\n   277→{\n   278→  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n   279→  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n   280→  \"type\": \"script\",\n   281→  \"config\": {\n   282→    \"run\": \"gosec ./...\",\n   283→    \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n   284→  }\n   285→}\n   286→```\n   287→\n   288→Parses the workflow file, inserts the step definition, serializes back.\n   289→\n   290→**Add Wiring:**\n   291→```json\n   292→{\n   293→  \"op\": \"add_wire\",\n   294→  \"wires\": [\n   295→    {\"from\": \"test\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"security-scan\"},\n   296→    {\"from\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"fail\", \"to\": \"fix\"}\n   297→  ]\n   298→}\n   299→```\n   300→\n   301→Appends wires to the wiring section.\n   302→\n   303→**Rewire Result:**\n   304→```json\n   305→{\n   306→  \"op\": \"rewire_result\",\n   307→  \"from\": \"test\",\n   308→  \"result\": \"success\",\n   309→  \"old_to\": \"done\",\n   310→  \"new_to\": \"security-scan\"\n   311→}\n   312→```\n   313→\n   314→Changes the target of an existing wire. Used by the orchestrator when inserting\n   315→a new step into the graph: it finds a wire pointing to `done`, rewires it to\n   316→the new step, then wires the new step's results to terminals. This splices the\n   317→new step into the existing flow rather than creating a disconnected node.\n   318→\n   319→**Update Collect:**\n   320→```json\n   321→{\n   322→  \"op\": \"update_collect\",\n   323→  \"collect_target\": \"done\",\n   324→  \"add_conditions\": [\n   325→    {\"step\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"success\"}\n   326→  ]\n   327→}\n   328→```\n   329→\n   330→Finds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n   331→\n   332→**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n   333→`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n   334→rejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n   335→\n   336→**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer —\n   337→parse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\n   338→back. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n   339→\n   340→Branches B and C often fire together — a new script step needs both the script\n   341→file (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n   342→\n   343→### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n   344→\n   345→After all changes are applied:\n   346→\n   347→1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   348→   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   349→2. **Restore** — restores a file from a named snapshot (used by the Curator\n   350→   to roll back corrupted writes)\n   351→3. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   352→   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n   353→4. **Knowledge base update** — merges the Reflector's lessons into\n   354→   `knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl` with ID-based deduplication and optional\n   355→   pruning via `MaxPromptBullets`\n   356→\n   357→## Knowledge Base Structure\n   358→\n   359→The knowledge base is a JSONL file — one JSON object per line, each\n   360→representing a `Lesson`. Lessons are keyed by `id` for deduplication: if a\n   361→lesson with the same ID already exists, it is updated in place rather than\n   362→appended. When `MaxPromptBullets` is configured and the total number of\n   363→lessons exceeds that limit, the oldest entries are pruned to stay within\n   364→bounds.\n   365→\n   366→```jsonl\n   367→{\"id\":\"P001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add sanitization rule to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   368→{\"id\":\"W001\",\"category\":\"new_step\",\"step_type\":\"script\",\"insight\":\"Added gosec security scan step\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add gosec step to workflow\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   369→{\"id\":\"F001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Test timeout failures correlate with database connection setup\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add retry guidance to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-ghi\",\"run-jkl\"],\"confidence\":\"medium\"}\n   370→```\n   371→\n   372→The structured JSONL format enables reliable deduplication by lesson ID and\n   373→programmatic querying. Lessons that are superseded by newer insights with the\n   374→same ID are replaced automatically.\n   375→\n   376→## Trigger Logic\n   377→\n   378→### When Evolution Runs\n   379→\n   380→The pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\n   381→or failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n   382→\n   383→- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n   384→  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n   385→  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n   386→- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n   387→  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n   388→- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n   389→  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n   390→  the executor branches.\n   391→\n   392→### History Window\n   393→\n   394→The Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   395→`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\n   396→memory — once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\n   397→even as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\n   398→and continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n   399→\n   400→## Protocol Changes\n   401→\n   402→### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)\n   403→\n   404→```protobuf\n   405→message RunRequest {\n   406→  string workflow = 1;\n   407→  string prompt = 2;\n   408→  string project_dir = 3;   // NEW\n   409→}\n   410→```\n   411→\n   412→### Status Protocol (Agent to Daemon)\n   413→\n   414→```protobuf\n   415→message StepStarted {\n   416→  string step_name = 1;\n   417→  string prompt_text = 2;    // NEW: assembled prompt\n   418→}\n   419→\n   420→message StepCompleted {\n   421→  string step_name = 1;\n   422→  string result = 2;\n   423→  string agent_output = 3;   // NEW: LLM response\n   424→  int32 attempt_number = 4;  // NEW\n   425→}\n   426→```\n   427→\n   428→### Prompt Adapter Changes\n   429→\n   430→The prompt adapter captures the assembled prompt text before invoking the agent\n   431→and the agent's stdout after it returns. Both are forwarded to the daemon via\n   432→the status protocol. No changes to prompt assembly logic — the evolution system\n   433→modifies prompt files on disk, and the existing `file()` mechanism picks up\n   434→changes on the next run.\n   435→\n   436→## Configuration\n   437→\n   438→Per-project in `.cloche/config`:\n   439→\n   440→```toml\n   441→[evolution]\n   442→enabled = true                # master switch\n   443→debounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\n   444→min_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\n   445→max_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n   446→```\n   447→\n   448→Evolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\n   449→workflows.\n   450→\n   451→## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   452→\n   453→- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   454→  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   455→- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n   456→- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   457→  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   458→- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   459→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NmesgiHcE4G9dhVoyT8RMp","session_id":"f471cee6-1691-4c3d-afcc-78ec7889b431","uuid":"e62c7892-aabf-4b3c-aaf6-9ca9ff1ecdf3","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:01.514Z"}
