{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015qwBzupPWVdYY3stvLMPri","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package evolution\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"strings\"\n     8→)\n     9→\n    10→// Reflector examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons.\n    11→type Reflector struct {\n    12→\tLLM           LLMClient\n    13→\tMinConfidence string // \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\"\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→type reflectResponse struct {\n    17→\tLessons []Lesson `json:\"lessons\"`\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→// confidenceLevel returns a numeric level for comparison.\n    21→func confidenceLevel(c string) int {\n    22→\tswitch c {\n    23→\tcase \"high\":\n    24→\t\treturn 3\n    25→\tcase \"medium\":\n    26→\t\treturn 2\n    27→\tcase \"low\":\n    28→\t\treturn 1\n    29→\tdefault:\n    30→\t\treturn 0\n    31→\t}\n    32→}\n    33→\n    34→// Reflect analyzes collected data and returns actionable lessons.\n    35→func (r *Reflector) Reflect(ctx context.Context, data *CollectedData, classification string) ([]Lesson, error) {\n    36→\tsystemPrompt := `You are an evolution agent that analyzes software development workflow execution history.\n    37→You examine run results, failure patterns, retry counts, and user feedback to extract structured lessons.\n    38→\n    39→For each lesson, provide:\n    40→- id: a unique identifier (e.g., \"lesson-YYYYMMDD-NNN\")\n    41→- category: one of \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n    42→- step_type: for new_step, either \"script\" or \"agent\"\n    43→- target: for prompt_improvement, the prompt file path to update\n    44→- insight: what pattern you observed\n    45→- suggested_action: the concrete change to make\n    46→- evidence: list of run IDs that support this lesson\n    47→- confidence: \"high\" (4+ occurrences, clear pattern), \"medium\" (2-3 occurrences), \"low\" (1 occurrence or ambiguous)\n    48→\n    49→Only suggest changes that address real, repeated patterns. Do not suggest changes for one-off issues.\n    50→Respond with JSON: {\"lessons\": [...]}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NmesgiHcE4G9dhVoyT8RMp","session_id":"f471cee6-1691-4c3d-afcc-78ec7889b431","uuid":"2575ef75-d867-4eec-a568-eb00884ec9a6","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:06.676Z"}
