{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NmesgiHcE4G9dhVoyT8RMp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Exploration Report: `internal/evolution/` Directory\n\n### Summary\n\nThe `internal/evolution/` directory implements a self-evolution pipeline for the Cloche system. It analyzes workflow run history and automatically improves prompts, adds validation steps, and refines workflows over time. **There is no Pareto front or fitness scoring system in the current codebase** — the system uses a single-objective approach based on confidence levels and pattern detection.\n\n---\n\n### File Structure (14 files, ~136KB)\n\n| File | Size | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `types.go` | 2.0K | Core type definitions (LLMClient, CollectedData, Lesson, EvolutionResult, Change) |\n| `orchestrator.go` | 6.9K | Main pipeline orchestration; wires all stages together |\n| `collector.go` | 2.6K | Gathers run history, knowledge base, prompts, workflow DSL |\n| `classifier.go` | 1.5K | LLM-based run classification (bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore) |\n| `reflector.go` | 3.7K | LLM-based lesson extraction from execution traces |\n| `curator.go` | 6.2K | ACE-style prompt improvement via LLM curation with safeguards |\n| `audit.go` | 4.8K | Audit logging, snapshots, knowledge base persistence |\n| `scriptgen.go` | 3.7K | LLM-based script/prompt generation for new steps |\n| `trigger.go` | 1.4K | Debounce mechanism for triggering evolution passes |\n| `llmclient.go` | 1.6K | CommandLLMClient adapter (invokes LLM via shell) |\n| `evolution_test.go` | 40K | Comprehensive tests for all pipeline stages |\n| `corruption_test.go` | 33K | Edge case and error handling tests |\n| `scriptgen_test.go` | 3.8K | Script generator tests |\n| `trigger_test.go` | 2.1K | Trigger debounce tests |\n\n---\n\n### Core Types (from `types.go`)\n\n```go\n// LLMClient interface — abstraction for any LLM backend\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n\n// CollectedData — aggregated input for Classifier and Reflector\ntype CollectedData struct {\n    Runs            []*domain.Run                      // runs since last evolution\n    Captures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // execution traces\n    KnowledgeBase   string                             // JSONL-formatted lessons\n    CurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // prompt file contents\n    CurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche DSL file content\n    WorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n    ProjectDir      string\n    WorkflowName    string\n}\n\n// Lesson — structured insight extracted by Reflector\ntype Lesson struct {\n    ID              string   `json:\"id\"`\n    Category        string   `json:\"category\"`               // \"prompt_improvement\" | \"new_step\"\n    StepType        string   `json:\"step_type,omitempty\"`    // \"script\" | \"agent\"\n    Target          string   `json:\"target,omitempty\"`       // prompt file path\n    Insight         string   `json:\"insight\"`                // pattern observed\n    SuggestedAction string   `json:\"suggested_action\"`       // concrete change\n    Evidence        []string `json:\"evidence\"`               // supporting run IDs\n    Confidence      string   `json:\"confidence\"`             // \"high\"|\"medium\"|\"low\"\n}\n\n// EvolutionResult — output of an evolution pass\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   `json:\"id\"`\n    ProjectDir     string   `json:\"project_dir\"`\n    WorkflowName   string   `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n    TriggerRunID   string   `json:\"trigger_run_id\"`\n    Timestamp      string   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    Classification string   `json:\"classification\"`       // run class\n    Changes        []Change `json:\"changes\"`               // files modified\n    KnowledgeDelta string   `json:\"knowledge_delta\"`       // summary\n}\n\n// Change — single file modification\ntype Change struct {\n    Type     string `json:\"type\"`        // \"prompt_update\"|\"add_script\"|\"add_step\"\n    File     string `json:\"file\"`        // relative path\n    Reason   string `json:\"reason\"`      // lesson insight\n    Snapshot string `json:\"snapshot\"`    // pre-change backup filename\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Pipeline Architecture (5 Stages + 3 Executor Branches)\n\n**Stage 1: Collector** (`collector.go`)\n- Gathers: recent runs, knowledge base, prompts, workflow DSL\n- Extracts prompt file paths from workflow via regex: `file(\"path\")`\n- Reads from disk (unless stores are nil for testing)\n\n**Stage 2: Classifier** (`classifier.go`)\n- LLM categorizes each run prompt into: bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, chore\n- Defaults to \"feature\" on error or invalid JSON\n- Single method: `Classify(ctx, runPrompt string) -> (string, error)`\n\n**Stage 3: Reflector** (`reflector.go`)\n- LLM examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons\n- Confidence filtering: low/medium/high based on evidence count\n- Deduplicates against knowledge base by lesson ID\n- Returns only lessons meeting `MinConfidence` threshold\n\n**Stage 4: Executor Branches** (one of three based on lesson category)\n\n- **Branch A: Curator** (`curator.go`)\n  - Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE principles\n  - Guards: substring check (`lessonAlreadyPresent`) prevents duplicate incorporation\n  - LLM curation with conversational response detection + fallback\n  - Post-write sanity check: re-reads file, validates structure, rolls back if corrupt\n  - Markdown code fence stripping + validation\n  \n- **Branch B: Script Generator** (`scriptgen.go`)\n  - Generates shell/Python scripts via LLM\n  - Validates: path containment, shebang requirement, no pre-existing file\n  - Returns: path + content\n  \n- **Branch C: DSL Mutator** (via `internal/dsl` package)\n  - Adds steps, wiring, rewires existing edges\n  - Validation: parses result, calls `workflow.Validate()`\n  - Splices new steps into graph by rewiring to intermediate point\n\n**Stage 5: Audit Logger** (`audit.go`)\n- Snapshots: copies pre-change files to `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n- Logs: appends JSONL entries to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n- Knowledge base update: JSONL with ID-based deduplication + optional pruning (`MaxPromptBullets`)\n\n---\n\n### Coding Conventions\n\n#### Error Handling\n- **Wrapped errors**: Uses `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)` consistently\n- **Nil returns on parse errors**: Classifier defaults to \"feature\" on JSON parse failure\n- **Graceful degradation**: Curator falls back to direct append if LLM returns conversational text\n- **Rollback on validation failure**: Curator restores from snapshot if sanity check fails\n\n#### Naming Patterns\n- **Functions**: PascalCase for exported, camelCase for unexported\n- **Private helpers**: `lessonAlreadyPresent`, `stripCodeFences`, `isConversationalResponse`, `promptSanityCheck`\n- **Struct receivers**: Single letter (`c *Curator`, `r *Reflector`, `o *Orchestrator`)\n- **Comments**: Block comments (packages) and inline comments for logic\n\n#### Project-Level Concerns\n- **Multi-project scoping**: All evolution state keyed by `projectDir + workflowName`\n- **Context passing**: All LLM calls use context for cancellation\n- **Atomic deduplication**: Knowledge base uses lesson `id` field for merge-on-update semantics\n- **Concurrency**: `Trigger` uses `sync.Mutex` for timer management\n\n---\n\n### Interfaces & Ports (from `internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n```go\n// EvolutionStore — persistence layer\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype EvolutionEntry struct {\n    ID             string\n    ProjectDir     string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    TriggerRunID   string\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    Classification string\n    ChangesJSON    string\n    KnowledgeDelta string\n}\n\n// CaptureStore — step execution traces\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Domain Types (from `internal/domain/`)\n\n**Run** (`run.go`)\n- `RunState`: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n- `Run`: ID, WorkflowName, State, StepExecutions, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage, etc.\n- `StepExecution`: StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n- Helper: `FindFirstFailedStep()`, `TaskAggregateStatus()`, `WorseState()`\n\n**Workflow** (`workflow.go`)\n- `Step`: Name, Type (agent/script/workflow), Results, Config\n- `Wire`: From, Result, To, OutputMap (for result mapping)\n- `WorkflowLocation`: LocationContainer, LocationHost\n- Methods: Parse, Validate, serialization support\n\n---\n\n### No Pareto/Multi-Objective Optimization Found\n\n**Key Finding:** The system uses a **single-objective confidence-based approach**, not Pareto optimization:\n\n1. **Confidence Filtering**: Lessons are filtered by minimum confidence (low/medium/high)\n2. **Evidence Count**: Confidence is based on occurrence count (4+ = high, 2-3 = medium, 1 = low)\n3. **ID-based Deduplication**: Lessons are merged by unique ID, not ranked across competing objectives\n4. **Sequential Execution**: Lessons are processed one-at-a-time within categories (prompt vs. new_step)\n\nThere is **no fitness scoring, ranking across multiple objectives, or Pareto front management**.\n\n---\n\n### Testing & Mocking\n\n**Test infrastructure** (`corruption_test.go`, `evolution_test.go`):\n- `fakeLLM`: Fixed response for deterministic testing\n- `errLLM`: Returns errors for error path testing\n- `callTrackingLLM`: Records LLM invocations for inspection\n- `mockEvolutionStore`, `mockCaptureStore`: Full store mocks\n- 73KB of tests covering: collector, classifier, curator, orchestrator, edge cases, corrupted prompts, path escaping\n\n---\n\n### Relative Paths for Key Files\n\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (EvolutionStore interface)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (Run, RunState, StepExecution)\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` (System design)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a857da760fae8cb50 (use SendMessage with to: 'a857da760fae8cb50' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53497\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 65223</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f471cee6-1691-4c3d-afcc-78ec7889b431","uuid":"c34a14c8-c2fa-41de-ab09-7f472a93a742","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:44.103Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the internal/evolution/ directory and any related files. I need to understand:\n1. What files already exist in internal/evolution/\n2. What types are defined (Candidate, FitnessScore, etc.)\n3. Coding conventions used (error handling, naming, comments)\n4. Any existing Pareto front related code\n\nAlso check internal/domain/ for any relevant types. Be thorough.","agentId":"a857da760fae8cb50","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Exploration Report: `internal/evolution/` Directory\n\n### Summary\n\nThe `internal/evolution/` directory implements a self-evolution pipeline for the Cloche system. It analyzes workflow run history and automatically improves prompts, adds validation steps, and refines workflows over time. **There is no Pareto front or fitness scoring system in the current codebase** — the system uses a single-objective approach based on confidence levels and pattern detection.\n\n---\n\n### File Structure (14 files, ~136KB)\n\n| File | Size | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `types.go` | 2.0K | Core type definitions (LLMClient, CollectedData, Lesson, EvolutionResult, Change) |\n| `orchestrator.go` | 6.9K | Main pipeline orchestration; wires all stages together |\n| `collector.go` | 2.6K | Gathers run history, knowledge base, prompts, workflow DSL |\n| `classifier.go` | 1.5K | LLM-based run classification (bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore) |\n| `reflector.go` | 3.7K | LLM-based lesson extraction from execution traces |\n| `curator.go` | 6.2K | ACE-style prompt improvement via LLM curation with safeguards |\n| `audit.go` | 4.8K | Audit logging, snapshots, knowledge base persistence |\n| `scriptgen.go` | 3.7K | LLM-based script/prompt generation for new steps |\n| `trigger.go` | 1.4K | Debounce mechanism for triggering evolution passes |\n| `llmclient.go` | 1.6K | CommandLLMClient adapter (invokes LLM via shell) |\n| `evolution_test.go` | 40K | Comprehensive tests for all pipeline stages |\n| `corruption_test.go` | 33K | Edge case and error handling tests |\n| `scriptgen_test.go` | 3.8K | Script generator tests |\n| `trigger_test.go` | 2.1K | Trigger debounce tests |\n\n---\n\n### Core Types (from `types.go`)\n\n```go\n// LLMClient interface — abstraction for any LLM backend\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n\n// CollectedData — aggregated input for Classifier and Reflector\ntype CollectedData struct {\n    Runs            []*domain.Run                      // runs since last evolution\n    Captures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // execution traces\n    KnowledgeBase   string                             // JSONL-formatted lessons\n    CurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // prompt file contents\n    CurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche DSL file content\n    WorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n    ProjectDir      string\n    WorkflowName    string\n}\n\n// Lesson — structured insight extracted by Reflector\ntype Lesson struct {\n    ID              string   `json:\"id\"`\n    Category        string   `json:\"category\"`               // \"prompt_improvement\" | \"new_step\"\n    StepType        string   `json:\"step_type,omitempty\"`    // \"script\" | \"agent\"\n    Target          string   `json:\"target,omitempty\"`       // prompt file path\n    Insight         string   `json:\"insight\"`                // pattern observed\n    SuggestedAction string   `json:\"suggested_action\"`       // concrete change\n    Evidence        []string `json:\"evidence\"`               // supporting run IDs\n    Confidence      string   `json:\"confidence\"`             // \"high\"|\"medium\"|\"low\"\n}\n\n// EvolutionResult — output of an evolution pass\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   `json:\"id\"`\n    ProjectDir     string   `json:\"project_dir\"`\n    WorkflowName   string   `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n    TriggerRunID   string   `json:\"trigger_run_id\"`\n    Timestamp      string   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    Classification string   `json:\"classification\"`       // run class\n    Changes        []Change `json:\"changes\"`               // files modified\n    KnowledgeDelta string   `json:\"knowledge_delta\"`       // summary\n}\n\n// Change — single file modification\ntype Change struct {\n    Type     string `json:\"type\"`        // \"prompt_update\"|\"add_script\"|\"add_step\"\n    File     string `json:\"file\"`        // relative path\n    Reason   string `json:\"reason\"`      // lesson insight\n    Snapshot string `json:\"snapshot\"`    // pre-change backup filename\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Pipeline Architecture (5 Stages + 3 Executor Branches)\n\n**Stage 1: Collector** (`collector.go`)\n- Gathers: recent runs, knowledge base, prompts, workflow DSL\n- Extracts prompt file paths from workflow via regex: `file(\"path\")`\n- Reads from disk (unless stores are nil for testing)\n\n**Stage 2: Classifier** (`classifier.go`)\n- LLM categorizes each run prompt into: bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, chore\n- Defaults to \"feature\" on error or invalid JSON\n- Single method: `Classify(ctx, runPrompt string) -> (string, error)`\n\n**Stage 3: Reflector** (`reflector.go`)\n- LLM examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons\n- Confidence filtering: low/medium/high based on evidence count\n- Deduplicates against knowledge base by lesson ID\n- Returns only lessons meeting `MinConfidence` threshold\n\n**Stage 4: Executor Branches** (one of three based on lesson category)\n\n- **Branch A: Curator** (`curator.go`)\n  - Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE principles\n  - Guards: substring check (`lessonAlreadyPresent`) prevents duplicate incorporation\n  - LLM curation with conversational response detection + fallback\n  - Post-write sanity check: re-reads file, validates structure, rolls back if corrupt\n  - Markdown code fence stripping + validation\n  \n- **Branch B: Script Generator** (`scriptgen.go`)\n  - Generates shell/Python scripts via LLM\n  - Validates: path containment, shebang requirement, no pre-existing file\n  - Returns: path + content\n  \n- **Branch C: DSL Mutator** (via `internal/dsl` package)\n  - Adds steps, wiring, rewires existing edges\n  - Validation: parses result, calls `workflow.Validate()`\n  - Splices new steps into graph by rewiring to intermediate point\n\n**Stage 5: Audit Logger** (`audit.go`)\n- Snapshots: copies pre-change files to `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n- Logs: appends JSONL entries to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n- Knowledge base update: JSONL with ID-based deduplication + optional pruning (`MaxPromptBullets`)\n\n---\n\n### Coding Conventions\n\n#### Error Handling\n- **Wrapped errors**: Uses `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)` consistently\n- **Nil returns on parse errors**: Classifier defaults to \"feature\" on JSON parse failure\n- **Graceful degradation**: Curator falls back to direct append if LLM returns conversational text\n- **Rollback on validation failure**: Curator restores from snapshot if sanity check fails\n\n#### Naming Patterns\n- **Functions**: PascalCase for exported, camelCase for unexported\n- **Private helpers**: `lessonAlreadyPresent`, `stripCodeFences`, `isConversationalResponse`, `promptSanityCheck`\n- **Struct receivers**: Single letter (`c *Curator`, `r *Reflector`, `o *Orchestrator`)\n- **Comments**: Block comments (packages) and inline comments for logic\n\n#### Project-Level Concerns\n- **Multi-project scoping**: All evolution state keyed by `projectDir + workflowName`\n- **Context passing**: All LLM calls use context for cancellation\n- **Atomic deduplication**: Knowledge base uses lesson `id` field for merge-on-update semantics\n- **Concurrency**: `Trigger` uses `sync.Mutex` for timer management\n\n---\n\n### Interfaces & Ports (from `internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n```go\n// EvolutionStore — persistence layer\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype EvolutionEntry struct {\n    ID             string\n    ProjectDir     string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    TriggerRunID   string\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    Classification string\n    ChangesJSON    string\n    KnowledgeDelta string\n}\n\n// CaptureStore — step execution traces\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Domain Types (from `internal/domain/`)\n\n**Run** (`run.go`)\n- `RunState`: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n- `Run`: ID, WorkflowName, State, StepExecutions, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage, etc.\n- `StepExecution`: StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n- Helper: `FindFirstFailedStep()`, `TaskAggregateStatus()`, `WorseState()`\n\n**Workflow** (`workflow.go`)\n- `Step`: Name, Type (agent/script/workflow), Results, Config\n- `Wire`: From, Result, To, OutputMap (for result mapping)\n- `WorkflowLocation`: LocationContainer, LocationHost\n- Methods: Parse, Validate, serialization support\n\n---\n\n### No Pareto/Multi-Objective Optimization Found\n\n**Key Finding:** The system uses a **single-objective confidence-based approach**, not Pareto optimization:\n\n1. **Confidence Filtering**: Lessons are filtered by minimum confidence (low/medium/high)\n2. **Evidence Count**: Confidence is based on occurrence count (4+ = high, 2-3 = medium, 1 = low)\n3. **ID-based Deduplication**: Lessons are merged by unique ID, not ranked across competing objectives\n4. **Sequential Execution**: Lessons are processed one-at-a-time within categories (prompt vs. new_step)\n\nThere is **no fitness scoring, ranking across multiple objectives, or Pareto front management**.\n\n---\n\n### Testing & Mocking\n\n**Test infrastructure** (`corruption_test.go`, `evolution_test.go`):\n- `fakeLLM`: Fixed response for deterministic testing\n- `errLLM`: Returns errors for error path testing\n- `callTrackingLLM`: Records LLM invocations for inspection\n- `mockEvolutionStore`, `mockCaptureStore`: Full store mocks\n- 73KB of tests covering: collector, classifier, curator, orchestrator, edge cases, corrupted prompts, path escaping\n\n---\n\n### Relative Paths for Key Files\n\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (EvolutionStore interface)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (Run, RunState, StepExecution)\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` (System design)"}],"totalDurationMs":65223,"totalTokens":53497,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1930,"cache_read_input_tokens":48611,"output_tokens":2954,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1930},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
